PMID== 17173826
TI  == [necrotizing subcutaneous infection by streptococcus agalactiae].
AB  == necrotizing soft tissue infections constitute some of the most potentially threatening infections that may be acquired in the community or in the hospital milieu as they are associated with a high mortality rate. in most cases they are  produced by streptococcus pyogenes. we report a case of a necrotizing soft tissue infection caused by streptococcus agalactiae (group b beta hemolytic streptococcus) that involved the leg of an elderly man with chronic lymphatic leukemia and diabetes mellitus. the lesions notably improved after initiating intravenous antibiotic treatment with amoxicillin-clavunate and clindamycin.
