TI  == bacteremia due to beta haemolytic streptococci.
AB  == the beta haemloytic streptococci (bhs) are well recognised human pathogens causing a variety of infections, including septicemia. it is important to ensure  their isolation from clinical specimens by using optimum media. moreover, since the different groups have different pathogenic potential, it is equally important to routinely serogroup them; this is emphasized here. since, bhs are uniformly will greatly decrease morbidity and mortality due to bhs infection.
