PMID== 7784807
TI  == arcanobacterium haemolyticum and streptococcal pharyngitis in army conscripts.
AB  == arcanobacterium haemolyticum was found in 1.4% and beta-haemolytic streptococci in 23% of throat cultures from army conscripts with sore throat (n = 498). 38% of the beta-haemolytic streptococci were of group a. patients culture-positive for a. haemolyticum or beta-haemolytic streptococci had pharyngeal exudate, cervical  lymphadenopathy and ear ache significantly more often--but cough less often--than culture-negative patients. the pharyngeal colonization rate of healthy conscripts (n = 232) by a. haemolyticum was 0.4% and by beta-haemolytic streptococci, 6.5%.
