AB  == aqueous extracts from lyophilized albumen glands of the garden snail (cepaea hortensis) exhibit, after separation from a second lectin, a specificity against  sialic acid-containing polymers. in agglutination studies with bacteria, the lectin interacts with all strains of group b streptococci (streptococcus agalactiae) containing type-specific polysaccharides. in contrast, group b streptococci containing only protein type antigens as well as all strains of other lancefield streptococcal groups and several other bacterial strains did not react.
