PMID== 1102599
TI  == the effects of chemotherapeutics on the species streptococcus in vitro.
AB  == the authors studied the sensitivity of some rather recent products--flucloxacillin, doxycyclin, clindamycin and cotrimoxazol--in correlation with classical penicillin. if therapy by means of classical penicillins is unsuitable, clindamycin and the semi-synthetic penicillin flucloxacillin appear to be a further alternative and the most suitable chemotherapeutic in streptococcal infections.
